<section class="walkthrough">
  <div class="inner">
    <h2>What gets generated</h2>
    <p class="intro">Running <code>structor init</code> writes a harness into your repository. It contains:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Canonical policy files (<code>ai/*</code>) that define how agents should interact with this repo</li>
      <li>Thin Codex and Claude Code entrypoints with context scoped to the repo</li>
      <li>Cross-repo contract files for products that span multiple repositories</li>
      <li>Task templates with consistent shape and expected outputs</li>
      <li>A routing hub (<code>ai/HUB.md</code>) that lets an agent started in any repo discover the whole product</li>
      <li>Read-only review views for auditing agent interactions</li>
      <li>Validation scripts that exit non-zero on drift</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="outro">The result is plain files in your repo with a stable shape and a way to detect drift.</p>
  </div>
</section>

